<p>Brandi Sigmon is an Assistant Professor of Practice in the Department of Plant Pathology at UNL. She holds a B.S. in Biology from Mars Hill College and a PhD in Genetics from Iowa State University. Her research focuses on using classical genetic, quantitative genetic, and comparative genomic tools to investigate grass inflorescences as a model to understand evolution and development.</p>

<h3 id="courses-taught">Courses Taught</h3>

<ul>
  <li>BIOS 206 General Genetics</li>
  <li>SCIL 101 Science and Decision-Making for a Complex World</li>
</ul>
